cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE. 

The paper proposes a regularization technique for Graph Neural Network based semi-supervised object classification, which is a problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also leverages recent advances in the regularization of classical deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the proposed method involves training a fully-connected network jointly with the graph neural network, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to several established and newly proposed graph benchmarks, indicating that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
